The United Nations estimates that four million people have become homeless as a result of the 2010 Pakistan floods; Secretary-General of the United Nations Ban Ki-moon, speaking in New York, states that the floods are a "slow-motion tsunami" as he calls for more funds to assist those affected. (Reuters) (BBC)Oxfam warns of a "double disaster" following flooding compounding a recent drought and food crisis in Niger. (AFP) (BBC)